## Callback functions

> With function callbacks you can inject your own functions into owl execution flow.

```
.owlCarousel({
	onInitialize: false
	onInitialized: false
	onOnResize: false
	onResized: false
	onRefresh: false
	onRefreshed: false
	onUpdate: false
	onUpdated: false
	onTouch: false
	onTouched: false
	onTranslate: false
	onAnimate: false
	onTranslated: false
	onChanged: false
	onLazyload: false
	onLazyloaded: false
	onVideoStop: false
	onVideoPlay: false
})

```

### Example:

```
$('.owl-carousel').owlCarousel({
	onTouched: callback
});

	function callback(){
		alert('Owl has been touched')
	}
})

```

### Callback parameters:

Each callback passes very useful parameters. Based on the example above:

```
function callback(element, info, callbackName){

	var el = element; 			// DOM element - in this example .owl-carousel
	var i = info; 				// info object contains owl status
	var name = callbackName;	// callback Name
}
```


### Info object:

Info object is updated during each Owl Carousel change in conjunction with onChange callback:

```
info.items  // number of declared items
info.allItems // number of all items
info.currentPosition // current position
info.currentPage  // current page
info.allPages  // number of all pages
info.windowWidth  // window width
info.elWidth // element width
info.breakpoint // current breakpoint

```
